June 15, 2025

Fatherâ€™s Day!

Sunday, nice and lazy start.. slept in.. got up, did the usual.. feed the horses and chickens for the neighbor next door while they are gone.. breakfast. Then got sucked into the tv monster with the Canadian Grand Prix.. then the US Open..

Jo asked what I wanted for early dinner.. went for French toast and bacon. While sitting at the counter I decided since we were leaving next week, I needed to cut down the tree the woodpeckers had killed drilling their nest before a hurricane took it down for me and tore up the fence. Really amazing.. the hole they pecked could have been laid out with a compass.. it was perfectly round. I decided to cut the tree up high to leave the stump for them to use again if they want.. I can always cut it to the ground later.

So after dinner, I jumped into project mode.. gassed up and oiled the chainsaw.. cut it down.. got out the trusty Mahindra and pulled the trailer up to load up the wood.. and drove it over to the neighbors burn pile. Wham Bam! Clean as a whistle. I love quick simple projects, clear start/finish. Out here though, they tend to come in piles.. but that part of the fun of living on acreage.
